  "body": "#### System information\r\nGeth version: 1.6.6-stable\r\nOS & Version: macOS Sierra 10.12.5\r\nActually the same behaviour is seen on Ubuntu 16.04 and same latest geth version (but Linux executable)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nWhen typing `exit` in the geth console that I started via `geth --syncmode=light console` I expected geth to quit. Even when trying a graceful shutdown via one time `Ctrl`+`c` it does not quit.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nInstead of quitting, geth seems to hang forever, I can only quit it by doing many `Ctrl`+`c`: This is the last output:\r\n\r\n> \\>exit\r\nINFO [07-05|19:25:40] IPC endpoint closed: /root/.ethereum/geth.ipc \r\nINFO [07-05|19:25:40] Blockchain manager stopped \r\nINFO [07-05|19:25:40] Stopping light Ethereum protocol \r\n^CINFO [07-05|19:26:55] Got interrupt, shutting down... \r\n^CWARN [07-05|19:31:01] Already shutting down, interrupt more to panic. times=9\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n`geth --syncmode=light console`\r\nThen wait for it to finish syncing and then in the geth console:\r\n`exit`\r\nNow as nothing happens do `Ctrl`+`c` which is also not going to quit it until you forcefully shut it down.",
